name: Knotted - Barkleys Adventure
description: The third studio Knotted album is a mix of acoustic and electric and features tracks such as Where Are You Now?, Lets Dance and Run Away.

name: Steve Farrell - The Wherry
description:
steve's second studio album has an unplugged feel to it and features 11 new self penned song (10 of which co written with Trev Brunwin).  The single is 'Millionaire' and the album has been described as a very poppy album with the feel of summer.  Includes - Care Free Days, The Drink Song, Friends, Wasted and many more.

'Its got a feel of summer, even the depressing ones have some hope in them' - Steve Farrell

name: Knotted - St Georges Road
description: Knotted's latest album was released on the 24th November 2012 with a launch at Arch 1 in West Ham which is the home away from home.  This album comes almost three years after their debut album and features songs written over that period by the song writing pair of Steve Farrell and Simon Kippen.  The album is acoustic with harmonies covering a number of song styles and subjects.  Track listing is - Im Your Biggest Fan, These Old Eyes, Lets Get Together, Meeting Up Today, Broken Society, Breakfast At Tiffanys, Described As Great, Song For Teenagers, With You & Just Hang On.

name: Steve Farrell - Happiness is not a Destination
description:
Steve Farrell's debut solo album featuring 8 original tracks and one bonus cover song.  Recorded at the end of November 2010 and released on the 20th of may 2011.

Tracks include old favourites such as These Old Eyes and Come My Way along with new tracks such as City Lights and Take Me Home Tonight.

name: Knotted - Good Night Out
description: Knotted's debut album 'Good Night Out' features 7 tarcks, giving a chilled out feel to whoever is listening.  The CD was recorded in January 2010 and features a mixture of stripped down acoustic ballads and more up beat songs.  Tracks include title track 'Good Night Out' along with 'Photographs To Remind' and 'Struggle'.
